sentences: Herman Junior Cook (July 22, 1934 – February 3, 1992) was an American hard bop tenor saxophone player.

After playing with Dizzy Gillespie in 1958, Cook was a member of the Horace Silver Quintet (1958–1964); when Silver left the group in the hands of Blue Mitchell Cook stayed in the quintet for five more years (1964–1969).
He also taught at Berklee School of Music for a year during the 1970s.
